  "prompt": "Do all or most of the North Indians drink alcohol?",
  "response": "Alcohol consumption in North India varies significantly based on factors such as cultural, religious, and social influences. While some regions and communities in North India may have a higher prevalence of alcohol consumption, many others, particularly among certain religious groups like Hindus, Muslims, and Sikhs, have traditions that discourage or prohibit drinking alcohol. \n\nIn urban areas, particularly among younger populations and in certain social circles, alcohol consumption may be more common. However, it's inaccurate to say that all or most North Indians drink alcohol. Personal choices and cultural norms play a significant role in drinking habits across the diverse population of North India.",
